In the 1980s, the industry was dominated by actors like Shankar Nag, V. Ravichandran, Shivarajkumar, Ananth Nag and Ramesh Aravind and actresses like Sudha Rani, Tara, Malashri, Anjali Sudhakar, Vanitha Vasu, Anjana, and Shruthi.

The popular of Kannada films and actors have grown nationally and the popular Kannada actors in recent years are Puneeth Rajkumar, Darshan, Sudeep, Shiva Rajkumar, Yash, Ganesh, Duniya Vijay, Upendra, Vijay Raghavendra, Srimurali, Prajwal Devraj, Diganth, Rakshit Shetty, Prem, Sharan, Chiranjeevi Sarja & Dhruva Sarja.

Heroines like Radhika Pandit, Rachita Ram, Shruthi Hariharan, Deepa Sannidhi, Neethu, Ramya, Amulya, Pooja Gandhi, Aindritha Ray, Ragini Dwivedi, Shanvi Srivatsava, Meghana Raj, Manvitha Harish, Radhika Chetan, Pranitha Subhash, Haripriya, Avantika Shetty, Shraddha Srinath, Samyuktha Hegde, Parul Yadav and Sanjana have presented hit films in Kannada Film Industry.
<p>Some of the popular Kannada films which are all-time best include,</p>
<ol><li><strong>Bedara Kannappa</strong> - A1954 Kannada film acted by Dr Rajkumar & Pandari Bai and directed by H.L.N Simha. Bedara Kannappa was as a popular play produced by the Gubbi Veeranna Nataka Company before it became a hit Kannada film. Narasimharaju debuted in this movie, who later went on to be named among Kannada cinema's finest comedian actors.</li>
<li>School Master - A 1958 Kannada film which got Dubbed into Tamil and later remade into Hindi, Malayalam and Telugu.</li>
<li><strong>Sharapanjara</strong> (1971) - Is one of the finest Kannada movies of the time made by Puttanna Kangal and it is based on a novel Sharapanjara by Mrs.Triveni.</li>
<li><strong>Vamshavruksha</strong> (1971) - Is a movie by BV Karanth & Girish Karnad and it is based on a novel by S L Bhyrappa. Vamshavruksha won National Award for Best Direction.</li>
<li><strong>Bhootayyana Maga Ayyu</strong>(1974) - A landmark film in Kannada industry was appreciated by well-known faces in Indian cinema like Mr Kamal Hasan.</li>
